                                <p>esure’s IT function is transforming and the Programme Management function has reformed as Solution Delivery with a different structure and way of workings based on vertical Solution Delivery teams comprising of Project Managers, Business Analysts, Developers and Testers.</p>

<p>We have 3 new roles available; Head of Retail, Marketing and Customer Solutions, Head of Underwriting, Claims and Operations Solutions and Head of Data Platform Solutions.</p>

<p>The environment is dynamic, with a very high demand on resources for Solution Delivery work. The successful candidate will have proven experience of leading business change and IT programmes and/or Development teams (senior business change and/or Technical Managers), Devising Solution Delivery Schedules to meet strategic aims of the business within the constraints of budget and capacity, agreed with exec Sponsors and the CIO, management and development of a full stack delivery team, its people, processes and technical solutions.</p>

<p>These roles can be based at any of our locations – Reigate, Manchester or Glasgow</p>

<p><span style="text-decoration:underline;"><strong><span style="line-height:1.6;">Responsibilities</span></strong></span></p>

<p><strong>Solution Management </strong></p>

<ul><li>To ensure esure’s PROJECTS are planned, scheduled, and resourced to meet the agreed scope and to the timetable agreed with the Exec Sponsor, OCP (Operational Change Programme) and CIO, while maintaining the PROJECTS budget and Solution Delivery budget.</li>
</ul><p><strong>Managing priorities</strong></p>

<ul><li>Working with the Exec Sponsors and OCP to determine business priorities and agreeing how the business initiative fits into the overall Solution Delivery Schedule, OCP and business strategy</li>
</ul><p><strong>Processes & Improvements</strong></p>

<ul><li>Ensuring adequate and efficient quality processes are embedded for solution delivery, and adhered to</li>
</ul><p><strong>Team & People Leadership</strong></p>

<ul><li>To manage the Solution Delivery team, including setting objectives, performance management, absence management and training and development.</li>
	<li>Management of Solution Delivery via management structure – between ten and thirty staff in total</li>
</ul><p><strong><span style="line-height:1.6;">Solution Delivery department</span></strong></p>

<ul><li>Participate as a member of management team in planning, problem resolution, and reviewing department performance.</li>
</ul>              </div>

